 <sect1>
  <title>The Terminology</title>
  <para>
   Although handled similarly in &productname;, modules and extensions are
   different:
  </para>
  <variablelist>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Modules</term>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      Modules are components which allow you to shape the product according to your needs. They are free of charge.
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Extensions</term>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      Extensions add functionality to your product. They are offered as subscriptions and require a registration key that is liable for costs.
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
